rComments: It has been many years since I took this course. I have always been upset that he had no time to help me when I approached him for help during his official office hours. (On multiple occasions)

Calculus was not too difficult in this class. However, the assignments given to us were absolutely disgusting. They'd take 5-8hrs or more per week just for 3%, not worth IMO. It just takes away from every other class and activities outside of school. The tests are fairly decent, you can look up old ones on the website and the final is quite similar

rComments: Professor Moore compassionately passes on the gift of mathematics to his students with a rare determination to see that no one is left behind. He puts himself on the forefront of the effort to ensure a level playing field for his students by confronting the misuse of Smart Watches during exams.

Pros: Moore is very helpful during office hours. His lecture notes are very, very helpful, to be honest I only go to lecture for his notes.   His assignments and tests are fair, hard but fair. Cons: Boring lecture,it is very hard to keep from  sleep. Writings on board  are just beyond recognition. Overall I would say his is a fair professor.

Absolutely the worst teacher who has ever set foot on this planet. Does not explain materials, late to lectures, does not finish lecture materials, and rambles about irrelevant things during lecture to stall time because HE DOES NOT KNOW HOW TO TEACH. Very unhelpful during office hours and hires the worst TAs.

Eric Moore is a professor that understands the material he is teaching very well. Unfortunately, he doesn't explain it very well to his students. He expects all students to understand the prerequisite material perfectly. Homework/ Assignments can take 8-12H a week (get marks for just doing the questions). TA's often don't speak English at all.

rComments: Hand writig is hard to recongnise, but Eric is cute.

I took his MATA23, MATB24, and MATB41. In the beginning, I found his lectures boring and not engaging. But for some reason I started to like him in the middle of MATB24. He was quite nice in person when he was in a good mood. And his notes were so useful when it came to midterm and exam preparation. Thanks to him, I feel more confident in math.

I know some people don't like him because his lectures are boring and a lot of notes to take. But somehow I don't hate him like other students do. When I visited him during his office hour, he was pretty nice to me and answered all my questions patiently and clearly. He is old, but he tries his best to teach stuff and understand his students.
hand writing are terrible.

I attended few of his lectures and still passed. Just do the assigned homework and readings and you will be fine. Beware of his final exam as they are quite hard. Only twist to both his midterm and final exams is that he has the tendency to ease his task by reusing questions.
Really boring class and prof. But he gives easy tests, most questions are from the past.
If he is the only instructor, don't take the course. Instead take the course equivalent at St. George. Worst instructor I had all year.

Horrible instructor. I hated the course so much. He really shouldn't be teaching. Instructor was horrible, T.A. was horrible, and the textbook was horrible. I learnt everything from the internet. I find it unfair for all the students to have to have him as an instructor.

He writes word for word the exact same notes in the handout onto the blackboard with hand writing so terrible that only the first 3 rows can see. Just stay home and read your textbook and do the assignments.
sitting in the front makes your experience much better. dont expect too much from the lectures. reading and doing assignments contributes to A+

He doesn't give any breaks. He barely explains concepts. Instead he gives a very dry and formal definition and dives into an example with minimum explanation. Consider taking your phone to lecture so you can take pictures of his notes as his writing is illegible at times. Supplementary resources (eg. YouTube videos) are a must in doing well.
He's a legend. nuf said
Really boring lectures but the notes are helpful, as are the assignments (especially when studying for the exams). Its in your best interest to look at previous exams when taking his courses.
